content.html:
AF/MF SETTING

RELEASE/FOCUS PRIORITY


Choose how the camera focuses in focus mode AF-S or AF-C.

OptionDescription
RELEASEShutter response is prioritized over focus. Pictures can be taken when the camera is not in focus.
FOCUSFocus is prioritized over shutter response. Pictures can be only taken when the camera is in focus.

AF RANGE LIMITER


OptionDescription
OFFFocus limiter disabled.
CUSTOMLimit focus to a range of distances defined by a minimum and maximum. ● OK: Limit focus to the selected range. SET: Choose two objects and limit focus to the distance be- tween them.
PRESET1Limit focus to a preset range.
PRESET2
Limit the range of available focus distances for increased focus
speed.

The values listed and displayed for the focus limiter may differ from the
actual focus distance.

The following additional operations can be performed when CUSTOM
is selected:
● You can tap objects in the touch screen display to choose the focus
range.
● Instead of tapping an object in the display, you set the maximum
focus distance to infinity by rotating the focus ring.

content.markdown:
AF/MF SETTING

# RELEASE/FOCUS PRIORITY

Choose how the camera focuses in focus mode AF-S or AF-C.

| Option | Description |
| --- | --- |
| RELEASE | Shutter response is prioritized over focus. Pictures can be taken when the camera is not in focus. |
| FOCUS | Focus is prioritized over shutter response. Pictures can be only taken when the camera is in focus. |


AF RANGE LIMITER

Limit the range of available focus distances for increased focus
speed.

| Option | Description |
| --- | --- |
| OFF | Focus limiter disabled. |
| CUSTOM | Limit focus to a range of distances defined by a minimum and maximum. ● OK: Limit focus to the selected range. SET: Choose two objects and limit focus to the distance be- tween them. |
| PRESET1 | Limit focus to a preset range. |
| PRESET2 | Limit focus to a preset range. |


The values listed and displayed for the focus limiter may differ from the
actual focus distance.

- The following additional operations can be performed when CUSTOM
- is selected:
- ● You can tap objects in the touch screen display to choose the focus
- range.
- ● Instead of tapping an object in the display, you set the maximum
- focus distance to infinity by rotating the focus ring.
